item_abyssal_blade.description: Active: Overwhelm - Stuns a target enemy unit for %stun_duration% seconds. Pierces Spell Immunity.\nPassive: Bash - Grants each attack a chance to stun the target for %bash_duration% seconds and deal %bonus_chance_damage% bonus damage, based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee.\nPassive: Damage Block - Grants the wielder a %block_chance%%% chance to block damage from incoming attacks based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.
item_abyssal_blade.lore: The lost blade of the Commander of the Abyss, this edge cuts into an enemy's soul.
item_abyssal_blade.name: item_abyssal_blade

item_aegis.description: Passive: Reincarnation - Brings you to life with full health and mana %reincarnate_time% seconds after you die, at the location where you died. Reincarnation must be used within %disappear_time_minutes_tooltip% minutes or Aegis of the Immortal disappears. If it expires, it will heal you over 5 seconds (dispels on damage).
item_aegis.lore: The Immortal was said to own a shield that protected him from death itself.
item_aegis.name: item_aegis

item_aether_lens.description: Passive: Increases spell cast range by %cast_range_bonus% and spell damage output by %spell_amp%%%
item_aether_lens.lore: Polished with the incantation of his final breath, the gift of a dying mage to his sickly son.
item_aether_lens.name: item_aether_lens

item_ancient_janggo.description:
Active: Endurance - Gives bonus +%bonus_attack_speed_pct% attack speed and +%bonus_movement_speed_pct%%% movement speed to allies in a %radius% radius.
Passive: Swiftness Aura - Gives bonus movement speed to allies in a %radius% radius.

Multiple instances of Swiftness Aura do not stack.
item_ancient_janggo.lore: A relic that enchants the bodies of those around it for swifter movement in times of crisis.
item_ancient_janggo.name: item_ancient_janggo

item_arcane_boots.description: Active: Replenish Mana - Restores mana to all allies in a %replenish_radius% area around the hero.\n\nFlat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack.
item_arcane_boots.lore: Magi equipped with these boots are valued in battle.
item_arcane_boots.name: item_arcane_boots

item_armlet.description: Active: Toggle Unholy Strength - When active, Unholy Strength grants +%unholy_bonus_damage% damage, +%unholy_bonus_strength% strength and +%unholy_bonus_armor% armor, but drains %unholy_health_drain_per_second_tooltip% health per second.  You cannot die from the health drain when Unholy Strength is activated, nor from the strength loss when Unholy Strength is deactivated.
item_armlet.lore: Weapon of choice among brutes, the bearer sacrifices his life energy to gain immense strength and power.
item_armlet.name: item_armlet

item_assault.description: Passive: Assault Aura - Grants attack speed and armor to nearby allied units and structures, and decreases the armor of nearby enemies.\n\nMultiple instances of Assault Aura do not stack.
item_assault.lore: Forged in the depths of the nether reaches, this hellish mail provides an army with increased armor and attack speed.
item_assault.name: item_assault

item_basher.description: Passive: Bash - Grants each attack a chance to stun the target for %bash_duration% seconds and deal %bonus_chance_damage% bonus damage, based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee.
item_basher.lore: A feared weapon in the right hands, this maul's ability to shatter the defenses of its opponents should not be underestimated.
item_basher.name: item_basher

item_belt_of_strength.lore: A valued accessory for improving vitality.
item_belt_of_strength.name: item_belt_of_strength

item_bfury.description: Active: Chop Tree/Ward - Destroy a target tree or ward. Chop cast range is increased when targetting wards.\nPassive: Quell - Increases attack damage against non-hero units, based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee. Does not provide bonus damage against Roshan.\nPassive: Cleave - Deals a percent of attack damage in an area around the target. Ranged units cannot Cleave.
item_bfury.lore: The bearer of this mighty axe gains the ability to cut down swaths of enemies at once.
item_bfury.name: item_bfury

item_black_king_bar.description: Active: Avatar - Grants Spell Immunity and 100% Magic Damage Resistance.  Duration and cooldown decrease with each use.  Some abilities are able to disable through Avatar.\n\nDISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_black_king_bar.lore: A powerful staff imbued with the strength of giants.
item_black_king_bar.name: item_black_king_bar

item_blade_mail.description: Active: Damage Return - Reflects any damage taken back to the unit that dealt the damage.  Lasts %duration% seconds.
item_blade_mail.lore: A razor-sharp coat of mail, it is the choice of selfless martyrs in combat.
item_blade_mail.name: item_blade_mail

item_blade_of_alacrity.lore: A long blade imbued with time magic.
item_blade_of_alacrity.name: item_blade_of_alacrity

item_blades_of_attack.lore: The damage of these small, concealable blades should not be underestimated.
item_blades_of_attack.name: item_blades_of_attack

item_blight_stone.description: Passive: Your attacks reduce target's armor for %corruption_duration% seconds.
item_blight_stone.lore: An unnerving stone unearthed beneath the Fields of Endless Carnage.
item_blight_stone.name: item_blight_stone

item_blink.description: Active: Blink - Teleport to a target point up to %blink_range% units away.  If damage is taken, Blink Dagger cannot be used for %blink_damage_cooldown% seconds.
item_blink.lore: The fabled dagger used by the fastest assassin ever to walk the lands.
item_blink.name: item_blink

item_bloodstone.description: Active: Pocket Deny - Instantly causes you to die.\nPassive: Bloodpact - Begins with 12 charges, and gains a charge each time an enemy hero dies within 1675 range. Each charge grants 1 mana regeneration per second, and reduces respawn time by %respawn_time_reduction% seconds. If the bearer dies, %heal_on_death_base% + %heal_on_death_per_charge% health per charge is restored to all allies within a %heal_on_death_range% radius, while the Bloodstone loses a third of its charges.
item_bloodstone.lore: The Bloodstone's bright ruby color is unmistakable on the battlefield, as the owner seems to have infinite vitality and spirit.
item_bloodstone.name: item_bloodstone

item_bloodthorn.description: Active: Silences a target for %silence_duration% seconds and amplifies the damage it takes by %silence_damage_percent%%%. All attacks on the silenced target will have True Strike and land a crit on impact.\nPassive: Critical Strike - Grants each attack a chance to deal additional damage. Critical Strike does not work against buildings.
item_bloodthorn.lore: A reviled blade that bites deeper with each wriggle of its victim's final throes.
item_bloodthorn.name: item_bloodthorn

item_boots.description: Flat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack.
item_boots.name: item_boots

item_boots_of_elves.lore: A tensile fabric often used for its light weight and ease of movement.
item_boots_of_elves.name: item_boots_of_elves

item_bottle.description: Use: Regenerate - Consumes a charge to restore Health and Mana over time. Healing stops if attacked.  Bottle can be refilled at your team's fountain.  Runes can be stored in the Bottle for later use, and are activated automatically after 2 minutes.  If Bottle does not have full charges and is placed on a courier, the courier will move 30%% slower.\n\nHold Control to use Regenerate on an allied hero.  Stored runes cannot be shared.
item_bottle.lore: An old bottle that survived the ages, the contents placed inside become enchanted.
item_bottle.name: item_bottle

item_bracer.lore: The bracer is a common choice to toughen up defenses and increase longevity.
item_bracer.name: item_bracer

item_branches.description: Active: Targets the ground to plant a happy little tree that lasts for %tree_duration% seconds.
item_branches.lore: A seemingly ordinary branch, its ironlike qualities are bestowed upon the bearer.
item_branches.name: item_branches

item_broadsword.lore: The classic weapon of choice for knights, this blade is sturdy and reliable for slaying enemies.
item_broadsword.name: item_broadsword

item_buckler.description: Active: Armor Bonus - Gives +%bonus_aoe_armor% armor to all allied units in a %bonus_aoe_radius% radius.  Lasts 25 seconds on heroes, 30 seconds on units.
item_buckler.lore: A powerful shield that imbues the bearer with the strength of heroes past, it is capable of protecting entire armies in battle.
item_buckler.name: item_buckler

item_butterfly.description: Active: Flutter - Trade evasion for %bonus_move_speed%%% additional movement speed for %duration% seconds.\n\nStacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.
item_butterfly.lore: Only the mightiest and most experienced of warriors can wield the Butterfly, but it provides incredible dexterity in combat.
item_butterfly.name: item_butterfly

item_chainmail.lore: A medium weave of metal chains.
item_chainmail.name: item_chainmail

item_cheese.description: Use: Consume to instantly restore health and mana.
item_cheese.lore: Made from the milk of a long lost Furbolg vendor, it restores the vitality of those who taste it.
item_cheese.name: item_cheese

item_circlet.lore: An elegant circlet designed for human princesses.
item_circlet.name: item_circlet

item_clarity.description: Use: Restores mana to the target unit over time.  If the unit is attacked by an enemy hero or Roshan, the effect is lost.
item_clarity.lore: Clear water that enhances the ability to meditate.
item_clarity.name: item_clarity

item_claymore.lore: A sword that can cut through armor, it's a commonly chosen first weapon for budding swordsmen.
item_claymore.name: item_claymore

item_cloak.lore: A cloak made of a magical material that works to dispel any magic cast on it.
item_cloak.name: item_cloak

item_courier.description: Use: Deploy Courier - Deploys a creature to carry items to and from your team's base.
item_courier.lore: Losing the courier is punishable by death.
item_courier.name: item_courier

item_crimson_guard.description: Active: Guard - Grant nearby allied heroes and buildings a %block_chance_active%%% chance to block %block_damage_melee_active% damage from each incoming attack, along with %bonus_aoe_armor% armor. Lasts %duration% seconds.\nPassive: Damage Block - Grants the wielder a %block_chance%%% chance to block damage from incoming attacks based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.
item_crimson_guard.lore: A cuirass originally built to protect against the dreaded Year Beast.
item_crimson_guard.name: item_crimson_guard

item_cyclone.description: Active: Cyclone - Sweeps a target unit up into cyclone, making them invulnerable for %cyclone_duration% seconds. Cyclone can be cast on yourself. Enemy units take 50 magical damage upon landing.\n\nDISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_cyclone.lore: A mysterious scepter passed down through the ages, its disruptive winds can be used for good or evil.
item_cyclone.name: item_cyclone

item_dagon.description: Active: Energy Burst - Emits a powerful burst of magical damage upon a targeted enemy unit. Upgradable.
item_dagon.lore: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.
item_dagon.name: item_dagon

item_dagon_2.description: Active: Energy Burst - Emits a powerful burst of magical damage upon a targeted enemy unit. Upgradable.
item_dagon_2.lore: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.
item_dagon_2.name: item_dagon_2

item_dagon_3.description: Active: Energy Burst - Emits a powerful burst of magical damage upon a targeted enemy unit. Upgradable.
item_dagon_3.lore: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.
item_dagon_3.name: item_dagon_3

item_dagon_4.description: Active: Energy Burst - Emits a powerful burst of magical damage upon a targeted enemy unit. Upgradable.
item_dagon_4.lore: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.
item_dagon_4.name: item_dagon_4

item_dagon_5.description: Active: Energy Burst - Emits a powerful burst of magical damage upon a targeted enemy unit.
item_dagon_5.lore: A lesser wand that grows in power the longer it is used, it brings magic to the fingertips of the user.
item_dagon_5.name: item_dagon_5

item_demon_edge.lore: One of the oldest weapons forged by the Demon-Smith Abzidian, it killed its maker when he tested its edge.
item_demon_edge.name: item_demon_edge

item_desolator.description: Passive: Corruption - Your attacks reduce target's armor for 15 seconds.
item_desolator.lore: A wicked weapon, used in torturing political criminals.
item_desolator.name: item_desolator

item_diffusal_blade.description:
Active: Purge - Targets an enemy, removing buffs from the target and slowing it for %purge_slow_duration% seconds.
Passive: Manabreak - Each attack burns %feedback_mana_burn% mana from the target, and deals %damage_per_burn% physical damage per burned mana. Burns %feedback_mana_burn_illusion_melee% mana per attack from melee illusions and %feedback_mana_burn_illusion_ranged% mana per attack from ranged illusions. Does not stack with other manabreak abilities.

Upgradable.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_diffusal_blade.lore: An enchanted blade that allows the user to cut straight into the enemy's soul.
item_diffusal_blade.name: item_diffusal_blade

item_diffusal_blade_2.description:
Active: Purge - Targets an enemy, removing buffs from the target and slowing it for %purge_slow_duration% seconds.
Passive: Manabreak - Each attack burns %feedback_mana_burn% mana from the target, and deals %damage_per_burn% physical damage per burned mana. Burns %feedback_mana_burn_illusion_melee% mana per attack from melee illusions and %feedback_mana_burn_illusion_ranged% mana per attack from ranged illusions. Does not stack with other manabreak abilities.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_diffusal_blade_2.lore: An enchanted blade that allows the user to cut straight into the enemy's soul.
item_diffusal_blade_2.name: item_diffusal_blade_2

item_dragon_lance.description: Passive: Increases attack range of ranged heroes by %base_attack_range%.
item_dragon_lance.lore: The forward charge of the wyvern host grants no quarter.
item_dragon_lance.name: item_dragon_lance

item_dust.description: Use: Reveals and slows invisible Heroes in a nearby area.
item_dust.lore: One may hide visage, but never volume.
item_dust.name: item_dust

item_eagle.lore: Capturing the majestic call of an eagle, this mystical horn brings limitless dexterity to those who hear it.
item_eagle.name: item_eagle

item_echo_sabre.description: Passive: Causes melee attacks to attack twice in quick succession. The double attacks apply a %slow_duration% second %movement_slow%%% movement slow on each strike.
item_echo_sabre.lore: A deceptively swift blade imbued with resonant magic.
item_echo_sabre.name: item_echo_sabre

item_enchanted_mango.description: Use: Consume the mango to instantly restore %replenish_amount% mana.\n\nHold Control to use Enchanted Mango on an allied hero.
item_enchanted_mango.lore: The bittersweet flavors of Jidi Isle are irresistible to amphibians.
item_enchanted_mango.name: item_enchanted_mango

item_energy_booster.lore: This lapis gemstone is commonly added to the collection of wizards seeking to improve their presence in combat.
item_energy_booster.name: item_energy_booster

item_ethereal_blade.description: Active: Ether Blast - Launches a projectile which converts the target to ethereal form, increasing any incoming magic damage they take, while rendering them immune to physical damage and unable to attack.  Can be cast on self.  If the target is an enemy, it is also slowed, and takes %blast_agility_multiplier%x your primary attribute + %blast_damage_base% as magical damage.\nUsing a Town Portal Scroll or Boots of Travel will not dispel Ethereal Form.
item_ethereal_blade.lore: A flickering blade of a ghastly nature, it is capable of dealing damage in both magical and physical planes.
item_ethereal_blade.name: item_ethereal_blade

item_faerie_fire.description: Use: Consume the Faerie Fire to instantly restore %hp_restore% HP
item_faerie_fire.lore: The ethereal flames from the ever-burning ruins of Kindertree ignite across realities.
item_faerie_fire.name: item_faerie_fire

item_flask.description: Use: Restores health to the target unit over time.  If the unit is attacked by an enemy hero or Roshan, the effect is lost.
item_flask.lore: A magical salve that can quickly mend even the deepest of wounds.
item_flask.name: item_flask

item_flying_courier.description: Upgrades your team's Animal Courier to a Flying Courier, granting it swift, unobstructed movement to carry items to and from your team's base.\n\nRequires a deployed Animal Courier.
item_flying_courier.lore: The faithful mount upon which soar the fortunes of battle.
item_flying_courier.name: item_flying_courier

item_force_staff.description: Active: Force - Pushes any target unit %push_length% units in the direction it is facing.  Double click to instantly cast Force on yourself.
item_force_staff.lore: Allows you to manipulate others, for good or evil.
item_force_staff.name: item_force_staff

item_gauntlets.lore: Studded leather gloves that add brute strength.
item_gauntlets.name: item_gauntlets

item_gem.description: Passive: True Sight - Adds the ability to see invisible units and wards to any allied vision within its carrier's range.\nDropped on death, and cannot be destroyed.
item_gem.lore:
Not one thrall creature of the depths,
Nor spirit bound in drowning's keep,
Nor Maelrawn the Tentacular,
Shall rest till seas, gem comes to sleep.
item_gem.name: item_gem

item_ghost.description: Active: Ghost Form - Enter ghost form, becoming immune to physical damage, yet unable to attack and taking 40%% extra magic damage.\nUsing a Town Portal Scroll or Boots of Travel  will not dispel Ghost Form.
item_ghost.lore: Imbues the wielder with a ghostly presence, allowing them to evade physical damage.
item_ghost.name: item_ghost

item_glimmer_cape.description: Active: Glimmer - After a %fade_delay% second delay, grants invisibility and %active_magical_armor%%% magic resistance to you or a target allied unit. Can be cast while channelling.
item_glimmer_cape.lore: The stolen cape of a master illusionist.
item_glimmer_cape.name: item_glimmer_cape

item_gloves.lore: A pair of magical gloves that seems to render weapons weightless.
item_gloves.name: item_gloves

item_greater_crit.description: Passive: Critical Strike - Grants each attack a chance to deal additional damage. Critical Strike does not work against buildings.
item_greater_crit.lore: A weapon of incredible power that is difficult for even the strongest of warriors to control.
item_greater_crit.name: item_greater_crit

item_guardian_greaves.description:
Active: Mend - Restores %replenish_health% health and %replenish_mana% mana to nearby allies, and removes most negative buffs from the caster.
Passive: Guardian Aura - Provides nearby allies with %aura_health_regen% health regeneration and %aura_armor% bonus armor. If an allied hero's health falls below %aura_bonus_threshold%%%, they receive %aura_health_regen_bonus% health regeneration and %aura_armor_bonus% armor.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_guardian_greaves.lore: One of many holy instruments constructed to honor the Omniscience.
item_guardian_greaves.name: item_guardian_greaves

item_hand_of_midas.description: Active: Transmute - Kills a non-hero target for %bonus_gold% gold and 1.85x experience.  Cannot be used on Ancient Creeps.
item_hand_of_midas.lore: Preserved through unknown magical means, the Hand of Midas is a weapon of greed, sacrificing animals to line the owner's pockets.
item_hand_of_midas.name: item_hand_of_midas

item_headdress.description: Passive: Regeneration Aura - Restores health to allies in a %aura_radius% unit radius.\n\nMultiple instances of Regeneration Aura do not stack.
item_headdress.lore: Creates a soothing aura that restores allies in battle.
item_headdress.name: item_headdress

item_heart.description: Passive: Health Regeneration - Restores a percentage of max health per second. If damage is taken from an enemy hero or Roshan, this ability is disabled for %cooldown_melee% seconds for melee heroes, or %cooldown_ranged_tooltip% seconds for ranged heroes.
item_heart.lore: Preserved heart of an extinct monster, it bolsters the bearer's fortitude.
item_heart.name: item_heart

item_heavens_halberd.description:
Active: Disarm - Prevents a target from attacking. Lasts %disarm_melee% seconds on melee targets, and %disarm_range% seconds on ranged targets.
Passive: Lesser Maim - Each attack has a chance to slow the enemy's movement and attack speed for %maim_duration% seconds.

Stacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.
item_heavens_halberd.lore: This halberd moves with the speed of a smaller weapon, allowing the bearer to win duels that a heavy edge would not.
item_heavens_halberd.name: item_heavens_halberd

item_helm_of_iron_will.lore: The helmet of a legendary warrior who fell in battle.
item_helm_of_iron_will.name: item_helm_of_iron_will

item_helm_of_the_dominator.description: Active: Dominate - Take control of a non-hero, non-ancient target unit and sets its movement speed to %speed_base%. If a dominated creep's base health is naturally below the health minimum, its base health will be raised to the health minimum.
item_helm_of_the_dominator.lore: The powerful headpiece of a dead necromancer.
item_helm_of_the_dominator.name: item_helm_of_the_dominator

item_hood_of_defiance.description: Active: Creates a spell shield that absorbs up to %barrier_block% magical damage.
item_hood_of_defiance.lore: A furred, magic resistant headpiece that is feared by wizards.
item_hood_of_defiance.name: item_hood_of_defiance

item_hurricane_pike.description: Active: When used on an enemy, it pushes you both away from each other %enemy_length% units each, and allows you to attack the target without range restrictions for %max_attacks% attacks for a maximum of %range_duration% seconds. Grants %bonus_attack_speed% Attack Speed during the attacks. Works like Force Staff when used on self or allies.\nPassive: Increases attack range of ranged heroes by %base_attack_range%.
item_hurricane_pike.lore: A legendary pike once held as royal sigil of the ancient wyvern riders.
item_hurricane_pike.name: item_hurricane_pike

item_hyperstone.lore: A mystical, carved stone that boosts the fervor of the holder.
item_hyperstone.name: item_hyperstone

item_infused_raindrop.description: Passive: Consumes a charge to block %magic_damage_block% magic damage from damage instances over %min_damage% damage. Comes with %initial_charges% charges. When the charges are gone, the item disappears.
item_infused_raindrop.name: item_infused_raindrop

item_invis_sword.description: Active: Shadow Walk - Makes you invisible until the duration ends, or until you attack or cast a spell.  While Shadow Walk is active, you move %windwalk_movement_speed%%% faster and can move through units.  If attacking to end the invisibility, you gain %windwalk_bonus_damage% bonus damage on that attack.  Lasts %windwalk_duration% seconds.
item_invis_sword.lore: The blade of a fallen king, it allows you to move unseen and strike from the shadows.
item_invis_sword.name: item_invis_sword

item_iron_talon.description: Active: Targets a non-player enemy unit to remove %creep_damage_pct%%% of its current HP.\nPassive: Quell - Increases attack damage against non-hero units, based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee.
item_iron_talon.lore: A simple but effective weapon devised to quell a great Hellbear uprising.
item_iron_talon.name: item_iron_talon

item_javelin.description: Passive: Pierce - Grants each attack a chance to deal bonus damage.
item_javelin.lore: A rather typical spear that can sometimes pierce through an enemy's armor when used to attack.
item_javelin.name: item_javelin

item_lesser_crit.description: Passive: Critical Strike - Grants each attack a chance to deal additional damage. Critical Strike does not work against buildings.
item_lesser_crit.lore: A blade forged from rare crystals, it seeks weak points in enemy armor.
item_lesser_crit.name: item_lesser_crit

item_lifesteal.description: Passive: Lifesteal - Heals the attacker for a percentage of attack damage dealt.\n\nMorbid Mask is a Unique Attack Modifier, and does not stack with other Unique Attack Modifiers.
item_lifesteal.lore: A mask that drains the energy of those caught in its gaze.
item_lifesteal.name: item_lifesteal

item_lotus_orb.description: Active: Echo Shell - Applies a shield to the target unit which re-casts most targeted spells back to their caster. The shielded unit will still take damage from the spell. Dispels negative buffs when applied.\n\nDISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_lotus_orb.lore: The jewel at its center still reflects a pale image of its creator.
item_lotus_orb.name: item_lotus_orb

item_maelstrom.description: Passive: Chain Lightning - Grants a chance on attack to release a bolt of electricity that leaps between %chain_strikes% targets, dealing %chain_damage% magical damage to each.
item_maelstrom.lore: A hammer forged for the gods themselves, Maelstrom allows its user to harness the power of lightning.
item_maelstrom.name: item_maelstrom

item_magic_stick.description: Active: Energy Charge - Instantly restores health and mana based on the number of charges stored. Gains a charge (max %max_charges%) whenever a nearby visible enemy uses an ability.
item_magic_stick.lore: A simple wand used to channel magic energies, it is favored by apprentice wizards and great warlocks alike.
item_magic_stick.name: item_magic_stick

item_magic_wand.description: Active: Energy Charge - Instantly restores health and mana based on the number of charges stored. Gains a charge (max %max_charges%) whenever a nearby visible enemy uses an ability.
item_magic_wand.lore: A simple wand used to channel magic energies, it is favored by apprentice wizards and great warlocks alike.
item_magic_wand.name: item_magic_wand

item_manta.description:
Active: Mirror Image - Creates %images_count% images of your hero that last %tooltip_illusion_duration% seconds. Melee heroes have a %cooldown_melee% second cooldown on this ability, while for Ranged heroes the cooldown is %cooldown_ranged_tooltip% seconds.

Melee images deal %tooltip_damage_outgoing_melee%%% damage and take %tooltip_damage_incoming_melee_total_pct%%% damage, while Ranged images deal %tooltip_damage_outgoing_ranged%%% and take %tooltip_damage_incoming_ranged_total_pct%%% damage.

Yasha-based movement speed bonuses from multiple items do not stack.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
item_manta.lore: An axe made of reflective materials that causes confusion amongst enemy ranks.
item_manta.name: item_manta

item_mantle.lore: A beautiful sapphire mantle worn by generations of queens.
item_mantle.name: item_mantle

item_mask_of_madness.description:
Active: Berserk - Gives %berserk_bonus_attack_speed% attack speed and %berserk_bonus_movement_speed%%% movement speed, but reduces your armor by %berserk_armor_reduction% and silences you.  Lasts %berserk_duration% seconds.
Passive: Lifesteal - Heals the attacker for a percentage of attack damage dealt.

Mask of Madness is a Unique Attack Modifier, and does not stack with other Unique Attack Modifiers.
item_mask_of_madness.lore: Once this mask is worn, its bearer becomes an uncontrollable aggressive force.
item_mask_of_madness.name: item_mask_of_madness

item_medallion_of_courage.description: Active: Valor - If cast on an ally, increases their armor while reducing the caster's. If cast on an enemy, reduces the armor of both the enemy and the caster. Cannot target magic immune enemies.
item_medallion_of_courage.lore: The bearer has no fear of combat.
item_medallion_of_courage.name: item_medallion_of_courage

item_mekansm.description:
Active: Restore - Heals %heal_amount% health and gives +%heal_bonus_armor% armor to allied units in a %heal_radius% radius.
Passive: Mekansm Aura - Grants %aura_health_regen% health regeneration to allied units in a %aura_radius% radius.

Multiple instances of Mekansm Aura do not stack.
item_mekansm.lore: A glowing jewel formed out of assorted parts that somehow fit together perfectly.
item_mekansm.name: item_mekansm

item_mithril_hammer.lore: A hammer forged of pure mithril.
item_mithril_hammer.name: item_mithril_hammer

item_mjollnir.description: Active: Static Charge - Places a charged shield on a target unit which has a %static_chance%%% chance to release a shocking bolt at a nearby attacker and %static_strikes% additional enemies.\nPassive: Chain Lightning - Grants a chance on attack to release a bolt of electricity that leaps between %chain_strikes% targets, dealing %chain_damage% magical damage to each.
item_mjollnir.lore: Thor's magical hammer, made for him by the dwarves Brok and Eitri.
item_mjollnir.name: item_mjollnir

item_monkey_king_bar.description: Passive: Mini-Bash - Grants each attack a chance to deal bonus damage and deal a mini-stun.\nPassive: True Strike - Prevents your attacks from missing. True Strike does not work when attacking enemy structures.
item_monkey_king_bar.lore: A powerful staff used by a master warrior.
item_monkey_king_bar.name: item_monkey_king_bar

item_moon_shard.description: Use: Consume the Moon Shard to permanently gain %consumed_bonus% attack speed and %consumed_bonus_night_vision% bonus night vision. Does not stack.\nPassive: Shade Sight - Grants %bonus_night_vision% bonus night vision.
item_moon_shard.lore: Said to be a tear from the lunar goddess Selemene.
item_moon_shard.name: item_moon_shard

item_mystic_staff.lore: Enigmatic staff made of only the most expensive crystals.
item_mystic_staff.name: item_mystic_staff

item_necronomicon.description: Active: Demonic Summoning - Summons a Warrior and an Archer to fight for you for %summon_duration% seconds, whose strength and abilities increase as Necronomicon is upgraded. Warrior gains True Sight at level 3. Upgradable.
item_necronomicon.lore: Considered the ultimate in necromancy and demonology, a powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.
item_necronomicon.name: item_necronomicon

item_necronomicon_2.description: Active: Demonic Summoning - Summons a Warrior and an Archer to fight for you for %summon_duration% seconds, whose strength and abilities increase as Necronomicon is upgraded. Warrior gains True Sight at level 3. Upgradable.
item_necronomicon_2.lore: Considered the ultimate in necromancy and demonology, a powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.
item_necronomicon_2.name: item_necronomicon_2

item_necronomicon_3.description: Active: Demonic Summoning - Summons a Warrior and an Archer to fight for you for %summon_duration% seconds, whose strength and abilities increase as Necronomicon is upgraded. Warrior gains True Sight at level 3.
item_necronomicon_3.lore: Considered the ultimate in necromancy and demonology, a powerful malefic force is locked within its pages.
item_necronomicon_3.name: item_necronomicon_3

item_null_talisman.lore: A small gemstone attached to several chains.
item_null_talisman.name: item_null_talisman

item_oblivion_staff.lore: Deceptively hidden as an ordinary quarterstaff, it is actually very powerful, much like the Eldritch who originally possessed it.
item_oblivion_staff.name: item_oblivion_staff

item_octarine_core.description: Passive: Cooldown Reduction - Reduces the cooldown time of all spells and items by %bonus_cooldown%%%.\nPassive: Spell Lifesteal - A percentage of damage caused by spells is returned to the caster as health.
item_octarine_core.lore: At the core of spellcraft are spectrums only the very gifted can sense.
item_octarine_core.name: item_octarine_core

item_ogre_axe.lore: You grow stronger just by holding it.
item_ogre_axe.name: item_ogre_axe

item_orb_of_venom.description: Passive: Poison Attack - Poisons the target, dealing damage over time and slowing movement based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.
item_orb_of_venom.lore: Envenoms your veapon with the venom of a venomous viper.
item_orb_of_venom.name: item_orb_of_venom

item_orchid.description: Active: Soul Burn - Silences the target unit for %silence_duration% seconds. At the end of the silence, %silence_damage_percent%%% of the damage received while silenced is inflicted as bonus magical damage.
item_orchid.lore: A garnet rod constructed from the essence of a fire demon.
item_orchid.name: item_orchid

item_pers.lore: A gem that grants heart to the bearer.
item_pers.name: item_pers

item_phase_boots.description: Active: Phase - Gives increased movement speed and lets you move through units.  The increased movement speed is based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.\n\nFlat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack.
item_phase_boots.lore: Boots that allow the wearer to travel between the ether.
item_phase_boots.name: item_phase_boots

item_pipe.description: Active: Barrier - Gives a shield that blocks %barrier_block% spell damage to all allies in a %barrier_radius% radius.\nPassive: Insight Aura - Gives allied units %aura_health_regen% health regeneration and %magic_resistance_aura%%% magic resistance in a %aura_radius% radius.
item_pipe.lore: A powerful artifact of mysterious origin, it creates barriers against magical forces.
item_pipe.name: item_pipe

item_platemail.lore: Thick metal plates that protect the entire upper body. Avoid dropping on feet.
item_platemail.name: item_platemail

item_point_booster.lore: A perfectly formed amethyst that nourishes body and mind when held.
item_point_booster.name: item_point_booster

item_poor_mans_shield.description: Passive: Damage Block - Blocks physical attack damage based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee.  Poor Man's Shield will always block attacks from enemy Heroes, but has a %block_chance%%% chance to block damage from creeps.
item_poor_mans_shield.lore: A busted old shield that seems to block more than it should.
item_poor_mans_shield.name: item_poor_mans_shield

item_power_treads.description: Active: Switch Attribute - Changes selected attribute between Strength, Agility and Intelligence.\n\nPower Treads can be built using a Belt of Strength, Band of Elvenskin, or a Robe of the Magi.  Flat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack, nor does the attack speed bonus from multiple Power Treads.
item_power_treads.lore: A pair of tough-skinned boots that change to meet the demands of the wearer.
item_power_treads.name: item_power_treads

item_quarterstaff.lore: A basic staff that allows you to strike quickly.
item_quarterstaff.name: item_quarterstaff

item_quelling_blade.description: Active: Chop Tree/Ward - Destroy a target tree or ward. Chop cast range is increased when targetting wards.\nPassive: Quell - Increases attack damage against non-hero units, based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee.
item_quelling_blade.lore: The axe of a fallen gnome, it allows you to effectively maneuver the forest.
item_quelling_blade.name: item_quelling_blade

item_radiance.description: Active: Toggle Burn - When active, scorches nearby enemies for %aura_damage% damage per second and blinds them, causing them to miss %blind_pct%%% of their attacks.
item_radiance.lore: A divine weapon that causes damage and a bright burning effect that lays waste to nearby enemies.
item_radiance.name: item_radiance

item_rapier.description: Drops on death.  Becomes unusable if picked up by an ally of its owner until it is returned to its owner. It is immediately usable by anybody if an enemy of the owner picks it up. A dropped Rapier cannot be picked up by a courier.
item_rapier.lore: So powerful, it cannot have a single owner.
item_rapier.name: item_rapier

item_reaver.lore: A massive axe capable of tearing whole mountains down.
item_reaver.name: item_reaver

item_refresher.description: Active: Reset Cooldowns - Resets the cooldowns of all your items and abilities.
item_refresher.lore: A powerful artifact created for wizards.
item_refresher.name: item_refresher

item_relic.lore: An ancient weapon that often turns the tides of war.
item_relic.name: item_relic

item_ring_of_aquila.description:
Passive: Aquila Aura - Grants mana regeneration and armor in a %aura_radius% area of effect.
Active: Toggle whether the aura affects other non-hero units.

Multiple instances of Aquila Aura do not stack.
item_ring_of_aquila.lore: The ring of the fallen Warlord Aquila continues to support armies in battle.
item_ring_of_aquila.name: item_ring_of_aquila

item_ring_of_basilius.description:
Passive: Basilius Aura - Grants mana regeneration and armor in a %aura_radius% area of effect.
Active: Toggle whether the aura affects other non-hero units.

Multiple instances of Basilius Aura do not stack.
item_ring_of_basilius.lore: Ring given as a reward to the greatest mages.
item_ring_of_basilius.name: item_ring_of_basilius

item_ring_of_health.lore: A shiny ring found beneath a fat halfling's corpse.
item_ring_of_health.name: item_ring_of_health

item_ring_of_protection.lore: A glimmering ring that defends its bearer.
item_ring_of_protection.name: item_ring_of_protection

item_ring_of_regen.lore: This ring is considered a good luck charm among the Gnomes.
item_ring_of_regen.name: item_ring_of_regen

item_river_painter.description: Pour this serum into the river to transform the water into liquid chrome for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect. Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter.name: item_river_painter

item_river_painter2.description: Pour this serum into the river to dry up the water for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect . Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter2.name: item_river_painter2

item_river_painter3.description: Pour this serum into the river to transform the water into a green slime for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect. Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter3.name: item_river_painter3

item_river_painter4.description: Pour this serum into the river to make the water oily for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect. Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter4.name: item_river_painter4

item_river_painter5.description: Pour this serum into the river to make the water electric for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect. Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter5.name: item_river_painter5

item_river_painter6.description: Pour this serum into the river to transform the water into a purple bubbling potion for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect. Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter6.name: item_river_painter6

item_river_painter7.description: Pour this serum into the river to transform the water into blood for 15 minutes. <font color='#FF5555'>Using this item on the river will permanently consume one charge from your Armory supply upon expiration of the effect. Charges do not get consumed if the effect is replaced by a stronger vial before expiration.</font> Vials can only be used if at least one charge remains in your Armory. Charges will only be used by successfully enchanting the river, and will not be consumed if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. You can only cast a vial on the river if there's not a stronger vial already in effect.
item_river_painter7.name: item_river_painter7

item_robe.lore: This robe corrupts the soul of the user, but provides wisdom in return.
item_robe.name: item_robe

item_rod_of_atos.description: Active: Cripple - Roots the target for %duration% seconds.
item_rod_of_atos.lore: Atos, the Lord of Blight, has his essence stored in this deceptively simple wand.
item_rod_of_atos.name: item_rod_of_atos

item_sange.description: Passive: Lesser Maim - Each attack has a chance to slow the enemy's movement and attack speed for %maim_duration% seconds.
item_sange.lore: Sange is an unusually accurate weapon, seeking weak points automatically.
item_sange.name: item_sange

item_sange_and_yasha.description: Passive: Greater Maim - Each attack has a chance to slow the enemy's movement and attack speed for %maim_duration% seconds.\n\nYasha-based movement speed bonuses from multiple items do not stack.
item_sange_and_yasha.lore: Sange and Yasha, when attuned by the moonlight and used together, become a very powerful combination.
item_sange_and_yasha.name: item_sange_and_yasha

item_satanic.description:
Active: Unholy Rage - Increases Lifesteal percentage to %unholy_lifesteal_total_tooltip%%% for %unholy_duration% seconds.
Passive: Lifesteal - Heals the attacker for a percentage of attack damage dealt.

Satanic is a Unique Attack Modifier, and does not stack with other Unique Attack Modifiers.
item_satanic.lore: Immense power at the cost of your soul.
item_satanic.name: item_satanic

item_shadow_amulet.description: Active: Fade - Grants invisibility to you or a target allied hero after a %fade_time% second fade time. Moving breaks the invisibility. There is no cooldown when using this item on yourself.
item_shadow_amulet.lore: A small talisman that clouds the senses of one's enemies when held perfectly still.
item_shadow_amulet.name: item_shadow_amulet

item_sheepstick.description: Active: Hex - Turns a target unit into a harmless critter for %sheep_duration% seconds. Instantly destroys illusions.
item_sheepstick.lore: The most guarded relic among the cult of Vyse, it is the most coveted weapon among magi.
item_sheepstick.name: item_sheepstick

item_shivas_guard.description:
Active: Arctic Blast - Emits a freezing wave that deals %blast_damage% magical damage to enemies and slows their movement by %blast_movement_speed%%% for %blast_debuff_duration% seconds.
Passive: Freezing Aura - Reduces the attack speed of all enemies in a %aura_radius% radius.

Multiple instances of Freezing Aura do not stack.
item_shivas_guard.lore: Said to have belonged to a goddess, today it retains much of its former power.
item_shivas_guard.name: item_shivas_guard

item_silver_edge.description: Active: Shadow Walk - Makes you invisible until the duration ends, or until you attack or cast a spell.  While invisible, you move %windwalk_movement_speed%%% faster and can move through units.  Attacking to end the invisibility will deal %windwalk_bonus_damage% bonus damage to the target, disable their passive abilities, and reduce their damage output.
item_silver_edge.lore: Once used to slay an unjust king, only to have the kingdom erupt into civil war in the aftermath.
item_silver_edge.name: item_silver_edge

item_skadi.description: Passive: Cold Attack - Each attack slows the movement and attack speed of the target. The duration of the slow is based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.
item_skadi.lore: Extremely rare artifact, guarded by the azure dragons.
item_skadi.name: item_skadi

item_slippers.lore: Light boots made from spider skin that tingles your senses.
item_slippers.name: item_slippers

item_smoke_of_deceit.description: Use: Upon activation, the user and all nearby allied player-controlled units gain invisibility and bonus movement speed for a brief time.  Minimap icons will also be hidden.  Attacking, or moving within %visibility_radius% range of an enemy hero or tower, will break the invisibility.
item_smoke_of_deceit.lore: The charlatan wizard Myrddin's only true contribution to the arcane arts.
item_smoke_of_deceit.name: item_smoke_of_deceit

item_sobi_mask.lore: A mask commonly used by mages and warlocks for various rituals.
item_sobi_mask.name: item_sobi_mask

item_solar_crest.description: Active: Shine - Temporarily removes the armor and evasion from Solar Crest. When cast on an ally it grants them %bonus_armor% armor and %bonus_evasion%%% evasion. When cast on an enemy, it removes %bonus_armor% of their armor and grants your allies to have %truestrike_chance%%% Accuracy on the target. Cannot target magic immune enemies.
item_solar_crest.lore: A talisman forged to honor the daytime sky.
item_solar_crest.name: item_solar_crest

item_soul_ring.description: Active: Sacrifice - Consume %health_sacrifice% health to temporarily gain %mana_gain% mana.  Lasts 10 seconds.
item_soul_ring.lore: A ring that feeds on the souls of those who wear it.
item_soul_ring.name: item_soul_ring

item_sphere.description: Passive: Spellblock - Blocks most targeted spells once every %block_cooldown% seconds.\nActive: Transfer Spellblock - Temporarily removes Spellblock from the item's owner and transfers it to an allied unit.
item_sphere.lore: This magical sphere once protected one of the most famous heroes in history.
item_sphere.name: item_sphere

item_staff_of_wizardry.lore: A staff of magical powers passed down from the eldest mages.
item_staff_of_wizardry.name: item_staff_of_wizardry

item_stout_shield.description: Passive: Damage Block - Gives a chance to block damage based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.
item_stout_shield.lore: One man's wine barrel bottom is another man's shield.
item_stout_shield.name: item_stout_shield

item_talisman_of_evasion.description: Stacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.
item_talisman_of_evasion.lore: A necklace that allows you to anticipate enemy attacks.
item_talisman_of_evasion.name: item_talisman_of_evasion

item_tango.description: Use: Eat a Tree or Ward - Consume a target tree or ward to gradually restore health.\n\nComes with 4 charges.  Can be used on an allied hero to give them one Tango.
item_tango.lore: Forage to survive on the battlefield.
item_tango.name: item_tango

item_tango_single.description: Use: Eat a Tree or Ward - Consume a target tree or ward to gradually restore health.
item_tango_single.name: item_tango_single

item_tome_of_knowledge.description: Use: Grants you %xp_bonus% experience plus %xp_per_use% per tome consumed by your team.
item_tome_of_knowledge.lore: That which raises beast to man and man to god.
item_tome_of_knowledge.name: item_tome_of_knowledge

item_tpscroll.description: Use: Teleport - Teleports you to a target friendly building. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.
item_tpscroll.name: item_tpscroll

item_tranquil_boots.description: Passive: Break - Whenever you attack or are attacked, the health regeneration and 25 Movement Speed are lost for 13 seconds.
item_tranquil_boots.lore: While they increase the longevity of the wearer, this boot is not particularly reliable.
item_tranquil_boots.name: item_tranquil_boots

item_travel_boots.description: Active: Teleport - Teleports you to an allied non-hero unit or structure. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain. Upgradable to allow you to teleport to allied heroes.\n\nFlat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack.
item_travel_boots.name: item_travel_boots

item_travel_boots_2.description: Active: Teleport - Teleports you to any allied structure or unit, including heroes. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.\n\nFlat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack.
item_travel_boots_2.name: item_travel_boots_2

item_ultimate_orb.lore: A mystical orb containing the essence of life.
item_ultimate_orb.name: item_ultimate_orb

item_ultimate_scepter.description: Passive: Ultimate Upgrade - Upgrades the ultimate, and some abilities, of certain heroes.
item_ultimate_scepter.lore: The scepter of a wizard with demigod-like powers.
item_ultimate_scepter.name: item_ultimate_scepter

item_urn_of_shadows.description: Active: Soul Release - Heals health over time to friendly units, but deals pure damage over time to enemy units.  The healing effect is lost if the affected ally takes damage from an enemy hero or tower.\nGains charges every time an enemy hero dies within %soul_radius% units.  Only the closest Urn to the dying hero will gain a charge.
item_urn_of_shadows.lore: Contains the ashes of powerful demons.
item_urn_of_shadows.name: item_urn_of_shadows

item_vanguard.description: Passive: Damage Block - Grants the wielder a %block_chance%%% chance to block damage from incoming attacks based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.
item_vanguard.lore: A powerful shield that defends its wielder from even the most vicious of attacks.
item_vanguard.name: item_vanguard

item_veil_of_discord.description: Active: Magic Weakness - Emits a weakening blast that increases the magic damage enemies take. Lasts %resist_debuff_duration% seconds.
item_veil_of_discord.name: item_veil_of_discord

item_vitality_booster.lore: A ruby gemstone that has been passed down through generations of warrior kin.
item_vitality_booster.name: item_vitality_booster

item_vladmir.description: Passive: Vladmir's Aura - Grants lifesteal, health regeneration, mana regeneration, bonus attack damage, and armor to allies in a %aura_radius% radius.  The lifesteal percentage is based on whether the hero affected by the aura is melee or ranged.\n\nMultiple instances of Vladmir's Aura do not stack.
item_vladmir.lore: An eerie mask that is haunted with the malice of a fallen vampire.
item_vladmir.name: item_vladmir

item_void_stone.lore: Jewelry that was once used to channel nether realm magic, this ring pulses with energy.
item_void_stone.name: item_void_stone

item_ward_dispenser.description: Double-Click to switch the currently active ward.\n\nUse: Plant the currently active ward to keep watch over an area. Observer Wards reveal their surrounding area to your team. Sentry Wards grant True Sight, the ability to see invisible enemy units and wards, to any existing allied vision within its range.
item_ward_dispenser.lore: Advancements in stacking efficiency have made wards easier to carry than ever.
item_ward_dispenser.name: item_ward_dispenser

item_ward_observer.description: Use: Plants an Observer Ward, an invisible watcher that gives vision of its surrounding area to your team. Lasts %duration_minutes_tooltip% minutes.\n\nHold Control to give one Observer Ward to an allied hero.
item_ward_observer.lore: A form of half-sentient plant, often cultivated by apprentice wizards.
item_ward_observer.name: item_ward_observer

item_ward_sentry.description: Use: Plants a Sentry Ward, an invisible watcher that grants True Sight, the ability to see invisible enemy units and wards, to any existing allied vision within its range. Lasts %duration_minutes_tooltip% minutes.\n\nHold Control to give one Sentry Ward to an allied hero.
item_ward_sentry.lore: A form of plant originally grown in the garden of a fearful king.
item_ward_sentry.name: item_ward_sentry

item_wind_lace.lore: Hasten to battle on wind-touched heels
item_wind_lace.name: item_wind_lace

item_wraith_band.lore: A circlet with faint whispers echoing about it.
item_wraith_band.name: item_wraith_band

item_yasha.description: Yasha-based movement speed bonuses from multiple items do not stack.
item_yasha.lore: Yasha is regarded as the swiftest weapon ever created.
item_yasha.name: item_yasha
